<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmi:id="-Mm7s8vlK5CaZZ_Msx8reCQ" name="new_concept,_HlRqANpbEdyP58ppo1Ieaw" guid="-Mm7s8vlK5CaZZ_Msx8reCQ" version="7.2.0" mainDescription="&lt;p>&#xD;&#xA;    Architectural goals provide the motivation and rationale&amp;nbsp;for decisions. These goals are&amp;nbsp;often driven&#xD;&#xA;    by&amp;nbsp;the software requirements, particularly system-wide requirements [&lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;&#xA;    href=&quot;./../../../core.tech.common.base/guidances/supportingmaterials/references.tech_6CCF393.html&quot;&#xD;&#xA;    guid=&quot;_9ToeIB83Edqsvps02rpOOg&quot;>ALL02&lt;/a>].&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p>&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p>&#xD;&#xA;    Architectural goals define how the system needs to respond to change over time. Architectural goals tend to address the&#xD;&#xA;    following questions:&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p>&#xD;&#xA;&lt;ul>&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;li>&#xD;&#xA;        What is the expected lifespan of the system?&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/li>&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;li>&#xD;&#xA;        Will the system need to respond to technological changes over that time, such as new versions of middleware or&#xD;&#xA;        other products?&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/li>&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;li>&#xD;&#xA;        How&amp;nbsp;frequently is&amp;nbsp;the system&amp;nbsp;expected to adapt to change?&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/li>&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;li>&#xD;&#xA;        What changes can we anticipate in the future, and how can we make them easier to accommodate?&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/li>&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/ul>&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p>&#xD;&#xA;    These considerations will have a significant effect on the structure of the system.&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p>" longPresentationName="new_concept,_HlRqANpbEdyP58ppo1Ieaw"/>
